101:511-516. A Go¬Ø model is used to investigate the binding of a variety of homodimeric proteins. Analysis of the free energy as a function of the intramonomer and intermonomer contacts allows discrimination between two-state obligate dimers (binding occurs together with folding) and three-state dimers (folding precedes binding and monomers are stable). The model reproduces the experimentally known association mechanisms.
